$interpreted: Thug: Boss! It's that clueless idiot──
Thug: He's been wandering about our territory for some time now, looking for a lost loved one or some crap like that!
Boss Man: Any bastard with a girlfriend deserves to die! Giv' em a beating!!
Young Man: ... Excuse me, has anyone seen this girl?
Young Man: I really want to find her. Please, I need your help...
Empathetic Passerby: Poor guy. Gets beaten until he's black and blue, yet he keeps looking...
Disdainful Passerby: Well, you reap what you sow! Maybe she ran off with somebody else long ago~
Young Man: Why...? I've tried everything and I still haven't come up with anything...
Young Man: ... I must be the most miserable person on earth... *sob*... *sob*...
Vice: Really? Have you really exhausted all possibilities?
Young Man: ... You again!? What do you mean by that!?
Vice: What do I mean? I'm you. You don't know what you're thinking?
Vice: To me, you're just too afraid to throw off the fetters of society~
Vice: Let me teach you some better ways to do this!
Vice: Alright~look straight ahead. Here's our chance!
Young Man: ... Dear member of the Divination Society,
Young Man: we cordially invite you to the annual Divination Competition...
Young Man: This year's champion will not only be awarded the title of Master, they'll also──
Young Man: ──be granted help from the Divination Master in realizing one wish!
Vice: Look at your clothes~ You could walk right into the Divination Society...
Vice: Hehehe... sometimes doggy doo doo falls straight from heaven and right into your lap~
Virtue: Stop! Usurping someone's lost belongings is a punishable crime!
Virtue: As an ambassador of love and peace, I cannot stand by and watch this happen!!
Young Man: A-Another one...!?
Experienced Diviner: ... Hehe, sorry to keep everyone waiting. Starting now...
Experienced Diviner: ... members of the Divination Society are free to register for the Divination Competition. Late registrations are not acceptable!
Virtue: There's still time to repent! Hurry up and return this to its rightful owner!!
Vice: There's no turning back! You're gonna give up on this once in a lifetime opportunity!?
Young Man: ──Both of you, SHUT UP!!!!!
Young Man: Ever since she left, every summer when shooting stars flash across the night sky...
Young Man: ... I make my life's only wish...
Young Man: ... For the rest of my life, I won't be with a woman until I find her!
Young Man: (This time... no matter whether I choose to do good or evil...
Young Man: ... no matter if I have to cheat... I'll do whatever I have to──)
Young Man: (──I must win this competition... so that we can finally be together!)
